# migrations/versions/.gitkeep
# -----------------------------------------
# This directory is auto-populated by Flask-Migrate (Alembic).
#
# HOW TO USE:
#   1. flask db init        — Creates the migrations/ folder structure (one-time setup)
#   2. flask db migrate -m "initial models"   — Auto-generates a migration file here
#   3. flask db upgrade     — Applies pending migrations to the database
#
# EACH FILE IN THIS DIRECTORY:
#   - Is named with a timestamp + your migration message
#     e.g. "20260312_143022_initial_models.py"
#   - Contains upgrade() and downgrade() functions
#   - upgrade() applies your schema changes forward
#   - downgrade() reverts them
#
# DO commit migration files to git.
# They are the version history of your database schema.
